eedback from the audience is normally genuine and useful.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_1965\" style=\"width: 310px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"http:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cantabits\/archives\/1915\/river-cam\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-1965\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-1965\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"http:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cantabits\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/01\/River-Cam-300x150.jpg\" alt=\"The River Cam\" width=\"300\" height=\"150\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-1965\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cantabits\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/01\/River-Cam-300x150.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cantabits\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/01\/River-Cam-500x250.jpg 500w, https:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cantabits\/wp-content\/uploads\/2014\/01\/River-Cam.jpg 1000w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-1965\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The River Cam is a potential thoroughfare that didn&#8217;t feature in any ideas I suggested or heard.<\/p><\/div>\n<p><!--more-->To see the original slides, click <a href=\"http:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cam\/future_mobility.pdf\">here<\/a>. Obviously, the slides only cover the core of the talk &#8211; <a href=\"http:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cam\/future_mobility_notes.pdf\">click here<\/a> to see the slides with notes on some additional details and items I talked about. There are <a href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/media\/set\/?set=a.230721877110538.1073741837.182815678567825\">a small number of photos of the event<\/a> too.<\/p>\n<hr \/><ol class=\"footnotes\"><li id=\"footnote_0_1915\" class=\"footnote\">The other talks I have given were not on this subject, so there was a lot of preparatory work I needed to do. [<a href=\"#identifier_0_1915\" class=\"footnote-link footnote-back-link\">&#8617;<\/a>]<\/li><li id=\"footnote_1_1915\" class=\"footnote\">I had talked about Cambridge Automated Metro <a href=\"http:\/\/www.g400.co.uk\/cantabits\/archives\/1659\">to a local newspaper and on r